<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,532,699]" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">
FEMALE GENITALIA (
<figureCitation box="[407,493,532,558]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,853,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-141@15.[189,1398,847,1923]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 10. Holotype of Ilyobius bimaculatus (Banks, 1920), female genitalia. A. Lateroventral view. B. Lateral view. C. Morphological interpretation of genital sclerites in B. D. Ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761459" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761459/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="36">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Sternite 8 unmodified, densely covered by long setae; gonocoxite 8 as small, paired, ovoid sclerites; gonapophyses 8 as lateral smooth, glabrous, ovoid plates. Tergite 9 ventrally extended in lateral view, expanded and articulated to gonocoxite 9, posteroventral margin straight; gonocoxite 9 ovoid, uniformly setose; gonostylus 9 small, semicircular, posterodorsally located on gonocoxite 9; ectoproct as a small ovoid sclerite, setose.
</paragraph>
